# JM Morning Dashboard

Personal morning briefing dashboard for John-Mark Echols, The Field's Edge.

## Structure

```
jm-dashboard/
├── public/
│   └── index.html          # The dashboard (served as static site)
├── netlify/
│   └── functions/
│       ├── weather.js       # AccuWeather current conditions + forecast
│       ├── spurgeon.js      # C.H. Spurgeon Morning and Evening from CCEL
│       ├── garmin.js        # Garmin Connect health data
│       ├── calendar.js      # Google Calendar today's events
│       ├── tasks.js         # Asana priority tasks
│       ├── prayer.js        # Echo Prayer + tracker spreadsheets
│       └── morning-sms.js   # Scheduled Twilio SMS (weekdays 6:30 AM CT)
├── package.json
└── netlify.toml
```

## Deploy to Netlify

### Step 1 -- Upload to GitHub
Create a new private GitHub repo called `jm-dashboard` and push all these files.

### Step 2 -- Connect to Netlify
In Netlify, go to Add new site > Import an existing project > GitHub.
Select the `jm-dashboard` repo. Build settings are auto-detected from netlify.toml.

### Step 3 -- Set Environment Variables
In Netlify: Site configuration > Environment variables. Add all of these:

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `ACCUWEATHER_API_KEY` | Your AccuWeather API key |
| `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` | Twilio Account SID |
| `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN` | Twilio Auth Token |
| `TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER` | Your Twilio phone number (+1XXXXXXXXXX) |
| `MY_PHONE_NUMBER` | Your cell number (+1XXXXXXXXXX) |
| `GARMIN_EMAIL` | Garmin Connect email |
| `GARMIN_PASSWORD` | Garmin Connect password |
| `ASANA_ACCESS_TOKEN` | Asana personal access token (from app.asana.com/0/my-apps) |
| `GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON` | Google service account credentials JSON (see below) |

### Step 4 -- Google Service Account
To connect Google Calendar and Google Drive:
1. Go to console.cloud.google.com
2. Create a new project called "TFE Dashboard"
3. Enable Google Calendar API and Google Drive API and Google Sheets API
4. Go to IAM > Service Accounts > Create service account
5. Name it "tfe-dashboard" and create
6. Create a JSON key and download it
7. Paste the entire JSON content as the value of GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON in Netlify
8. In Google Calendar, share your calendar with the service account email (editor access)
9. In Google Drive, share the tracker spreadsheets folder with the service account email

### Step 5 -- Asana Token
Go to app.asana.com/0/my-apps > Personal Access Tokens > Create new token.
Add it as ASANA_ACCESS_TOKEN in Netlify.

### Step 6 -- Deploy
Netlify will auto-deploy on every push to main. Your dashboard will be live at:
https://jmdailydashboard.netlify.app

## Morning SMS Schedule
The morning-sms.js function runs automatically at 6:30 AM Central time, Monday-Friday.
It sends a brief summary and link to the dashboard.

